text: Wolfgang Pietzsch (1957) Wolfgang Pietzsch (21 December 1930, Wittgendorf – 29 December 1996, Leipzig) was a chess Grandmaster (1965). He played in the Chess Olympiads of 1952, 1958, 1960, 1962, 1966 and 1968. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1930 births Category:1996 deaths Category:Chess grandmasters Category:Chess Olympiad competitors Category:German chess players Category:20th-century chess players
